-- PNC and U.S. Bancorp were final bidders for NatCity: sources
-- 
-- Fri Oct 24, 2008 4:24pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/10/24/us-natcity-bidders-idUSTRE49N80820081024

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - US Bancorp ( USB.N ) and PNC Financial Services Group Inc ( PNC.N ) were the two final bidders for U.S. regional bank National City Corp NCC.N, sources familiar with the matter said on Friday. 

 PNC won the auction, agreeing to buy the Ohio-based lender in a government-supported $5.6 billion transaction to create the No. 5 U.S. bank by deposits. (Reporting by  Paritosh Bansal ; editing by Carol Bishopric)